âš™ï¸ Installation

Move to project folder:

cd config


Create virtual environment:

python -m venv venv


Activate:

venv\Scripts\activate


Install dependencies:

pip install django
pip install djangorestframework
pip install djangorestframework-simplejwt
pip install django-filter
pip install celery
pip install redis


Apply migrations:

python manage.py migrate

ğŸ”‘ Create Super User (Admin)
python manage.py createsuperuser


Login Panel:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin

â–¶ï¸ Running The Project
1ï¸âƒ£ Start Redis
docker run -d -p 6379:6379 redis

2ï¸âƒ£ Start Django Server
python manage.py runserver

3ï¸âƒ£ Start Celery Worker
celery -A config worker -l info -P solo

4ï¸âƒ£ Start Celery Beat
celery -A config beat -l info

ğŸ” Authentication Flow
Login
POST /api/auth/login/


Request:

{
  "username": "yourname",
  "password": "yourpassword"
}


Response:

{
  "access": "token_here",
  "refresh": "token_here"
}

Use Token

Header:

Authorization: Bearer ACCESS_TOKEN

ğŸ“¡ API Endpoints
Tasks
Method	Endpoint	Description
GET	/api/tasks/	Get all tasks
GET	/api/tasks/<id>/	Get task
POST	/api/tasks/	Create task
PATCH	/api/tasks/<id>/	Update
DELETE	/api/tasks/<id>/	Delete
ğŸ” Filtering & Pagination
Pagination
/api/tasks/?page=2

Filter by Status
/api/tasks/?status=OVERDUE

ğŸ“ Activity Logs
GET /api/tasks/logs/


Stores:

user

action

old value

new value

timestamp

â° Celery & Redis Automation

Automatically executes:

Every 30 seconds (or configured)


Checks tasks:

if due_date < today

AND status != completed

sets OVERDUE

Logs changes automatically.

ğŸ§¯ Troubleshooting
âŒ Redis not running

Run again:

docker run -d -p 6379:6379 redis

âŒ Celery "unregistered task"

Ensure worker started after server
Restart Celery.

âŒ Token expired

Re-login to generate new one.

